               <msContents>
                  <summary> A complete manuscript of the <title>Silsilah-'i Ẕahab</title> (Golden
                     Chain), first of seven books from the <title>Haft Awrang</title> (Seven
                     Thrones) by the late Timurid-era poet <persName key="person_90042997"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/90042997/" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">‘Abd al-Raḥmān
                        Jāmī (d. 1492)</persName>. While it lacks a signature and date, its
                     condition and 18th century provenance suggest it must be earlier, probably 17th
                     century, and possibly completed in either <placeName cert="medium"
                        ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000231" key="place_7000231">Greater
                        Iran</placeName> or the <placeName cert="medium"
                        ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000208" key="place_7000208">Indian
                        subcontinent</placeName>.</summary>

